<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Welcome to define!</title>
  </head>

  <body style="margin:0; padding:0; background:#f5f6f7; font-family:Inter, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;">
    <div style="max-width:640px; margin:48px auto; background:#ffffff; border-radius:20px; padding:48px; border:1px solid #e5e7eb; box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.04);">
      <h1 style="margin:0; font-size:34px; font-weight:900; color:#000;">
        Welcome to dfn<span style="color:#000">!.</span>
      </h1>

      <p style="margin-top:20px; font-size:18px; color:#374151; line-height:1.6;">
        Hey
        {{#if name}}
          {{name}}
        {{else}}
          there
        {{/if}},<br /><br />
        Thank you for joining us this early.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top:16px; font-size:16px; color:#4b5563; line-height:1.65;">
        Define! was created for a simple reason: creators deserve systems that respect their work,
        their time, and their money. For years, getting paid has been the slowest and most
        frustrating part of the creative process. We're changing that—carefully, intentionally,
        and with a long-term view.
      </p>

      {{#if verificationUrl}}
        <div style="margin-top:36px; text-align:center;">
          <a href="{{verificationUrl}}" style="display:inline-block; background:transparent; color:#000; border:2px solid #000; text-decoration:none; padding:16px 32px; font-size:16px; font-weight:600; border-radius:9999px; letter-spacing:0.1px;">
            Verify your email
          </a>
        </div>

        <p style="margin-top:28px; font-size:14px; color:#6b7280; text-align:center;">
          If the button doesn’t work, use this link:
        </p>

        <p style="word-break:break-all; font-size:14px; color:#111827; text-align:center; margin-top:4px;">
          {{verificationUrl}}
        </p>
      {{/if}}

      <h2 style="margin:40px 0 0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#000;">
        Here’s what you can expect inside:
      </h2>

      <ul style="margin-top:20px; padding-left:18px; font-size:15px; color:#4b5563; line-height:1.7;">
        <li><strong style="color:#000;">A clean, focused dashboard</strong> built for creators, not corporations.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#000;">A secure escrow system</strong> that keeps both sides protected from delays or disputes.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#000;">Your own booking link</strong>, ready to be shared on Instagram, WhatsApp, TikTok, and anywhere clients find you.</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#000;">A smooth, organised workflow</strong> that removes unnecessary admin from your creative process.</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin-top:28px; font-size:16px; color:#374151; line-height:1.65;">
        And this is only the beginning. What you see now is the foundation — every next layer of define! will be built with the same clarity, purpose, and creator-first approach.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top:40px; font-size:14px; color:#9ca3af; text-align:center;">
        Thank you again for being part of this early stage.<br />
        Let’s build something valuable.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top:12px; font-size:14px; color:#9ca3af; text-align:center;">
        — The define!. team
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
